ld the gaurds in his room drop spells. true?<br><br>Guardian wurms in SF. Farmed them off and on prior to the patch with varied results. Only been back once since patch and didn't get any wurm pops =\<br><br>WW Dragons usually have 2 groups for these we're cov aligned tho so after a few farms it's back to Arena or Royals. Haven't started the Canyon yet but will soon most of the peeps that go to WW with me are near completion of their SS.<br><br>Juggs I know about. Planning a full day there soon.<br><br>Are there any other Spell farms? Anything in Kael like Tormax's room or behind him? Velks castle got good drops? SoL? Haven't even stepped foot inside Ssra yet but am planning to soon. What about deep inside Ahkeva?<br><br>Basically we need alot of Spells 55-60 for every class cept our chanters. Any help on areas to go would be appreciated. I'll be happy with 1 or 2 good spells (not uber rare just not the common crap like from frogs in seb or corpral empathy/cele heal) from an hour or 2 farm.<br><br>Feeling very lost as far as palces to go to get these peeps their spells. <p><img src="http://members.spinn.net/~paradise/tanise.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sahhar>Sahhar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/9/02 10:29:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=267.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drop spots for spell farms</span><hr size=1> Chanters all have their spells? Not unusual, because chanter spells drop like candy, whereas our spell drops are on the frequency of like a GD solar eclipse ( no, GD does not mean &quot;Great Divide&quot; in this instance). Yeah KEI is rare, but thats about the only spell I ever see enchanters /WTB , whereas there are at least 2-3 wizzies still /WTB spells that are pre-60. Sorry, but pissing me off big time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utanisemanasponge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tanise Manasponge</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/10/02 11:40:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=267.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drop spots for spell farms</span><hr size=1> We have 3 encs. 2 60s and a 52. So they have been in the spell farm game for a while. Both 60s have Kei now at the bargin basement price of 20 and 25k. Neither has a complete Sol book yet.<br><br>Main concern is wizzie, mage, and to a point druid spells. Sinceit's the wizzies I need spells for most that's why I came here looking for advice on where to head. We're in HoT now so that's cramping WW farming for now.<br><br>Where are the best spots to go in Luclin? Velious? <br><br>Kunark is pretty much handled with Seb &amp; SF. Was told HS but I been there alot in all wings and have still mostly seen nothing but the same crap common spells. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utanisemanasponge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tanise Manasponge</A> at: 3/10/02 11:41:09 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ualavaireldritch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alavair Eldritch</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/11/02 10:13:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=267.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drop spots for spell farms</span><hr size=1> Now that Verant has increased the drop rates for Kunark spells, Guardian Wurms are definitely the way to go.  Killed 3 of them last week, they dropped 1, 0, and 3 spells respectively.<br><br>Kelorek'Dar in CS is a good one for Velious spells, last time we killed him he dropped 2 or 3 60th level spells.<br><br>No clue about Luclin yet... <p><p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=61958>Alavair Eldritch</A><br>Evoker of Solusek Ro<br><a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/bfuriouspantaloons>Furious Pantaloons</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utanisemanasponge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tanise Manasponge</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/13/02 1:27:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=267.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drop spots for spell farms</span><hr size=1> I'm Quite fond of Guardians in SF.  Were passing through SF last night and found one up and got Pillar of flame.<br><br>Drops off juggs have improved got a nice bunch of spells the other night including 3 Marker's Discord.<br><br>Where in Ssra is best to hunt? Went there for first time last night messed around on main floor got 1 drop I thought I'd read basement is pretty good area. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm8.showPrevMessage?topicID=267.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcom